Wola [ˈvɔla] (German: Wolla, 1938-45: Grenzdamm) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Kozłowo, within Nidzica County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately 10 kilometres (6 mi) south-east of Kozłowo, 15 km (9 mi) south of Nidzica, and 62 km (39 mi) south of the regional capital Olsztyn.


